</p>
<p>Appropriate etiquette includes focusing on the deceased's positive qualities and the impact they had on the recipient's life. Avoid offering unsolicited advice or minimizing their grief.  Instead, aim to offer solace and understanding, letting them know you are thinking of them and are there for support during this challenging time. Remember, the goal is to provide comfort and a sense of shared sorrow, not to fix or solve their pain.</p>
    

